      <h1>History</h1>
<p>In 2010, Girl Guides of Canada-Guides du Canada launched a National Service Project (NSP), in celebration of its 100th anniversary. The NSP encouraged  members to work together to make a real difference in the world. The theme for  the inaugural year was based on the United Nation’s Millennium Development Goal  #1: eradicating extreme poverty and hunger. Today, we continue to achieve even  more with our members and the public. Here’s what we’ve accomplished over the  last few years:</p>
<h4 class="pg-heading">2012 NSP: Operation  Earth Action (extended till 2014)</h4>
<p><a href="http://nsp.girlguides.ca/" target="_blank">Operation Earth Action</a> was based on the United Nation’s  MDG #7 -  ensuring environmental sustainability. It focuses on performing service for the environment  in fun and inspiring ways. Girls pledge or participate in activities to improve  the environment in one of these areas:</p>
<ol>
    <li>Reduce use of plastic water bottles and/or shopping bags</li>
    <li>Reduce the distance their food travels </li>
    <li>Make homemade green products</li>
    <li>Plant a tree in a public space</li>
    <li>Reduce energy consumption</li>
    <li>Supporting animal habitats </li>
    <li>Recycle materials from trash to treasure</li>
</ol>
<p>Visit our Operation Earth Action <a href="http://nsp.girlguides.ca/" target="_blank">website</a> learn more and to see  our collective impact!</p>
<h4 class="pg-heading">2011 NSP: EmPOWERing  Girls</h4>
<p>EmPOWERing  Girls was based on the United Nation’s MDG #3 - promoting gender equality and  empowering women. It focused on learning about issues facing girls and women  around the world. One component of the NSP was to have girl and adult members sign  PLAN Canada’s petition asking the Canadian government, and the United Nations, to  create an <a href="http://www.un.org/en/events/girlchild/about.shtml" target="_blank">International Day of  the Girl</a>.</p>
<h4 class="pg-heading">2010 NSP: Eradicating  Poverty &amp; Hunger</h4>
<p>In its inaugural year, our NSP was based on the  United Nation’s MDG #1 – eradicating extreme poverty and hunger. More than  16,000 members committed to over 68,000 acts to end hunger and poverty through various  activities.</p>
    
